-- Bulls Sign Guard Richard Hamilton After Contract Is Bought Out by Pistons
-- B y   J a y   B e b e r m a n
-- 2011-12-15T18:50:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-12-15/bulls-sign-guard-richard-hamilton-after-contract-is-bought-out-by-pistons.html
The  Chicago Bulls  signed free-agent
guard Richard Hamilton, the National Basketball Association team
said in a statement.  Hamilton, 33, has averaged 17.1 points during his career
and was a member of the  Detroit  Pistons’ 2004 championship
squad. The three-time All-Star’s contract was bought out by
Detroit last week.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Jay Beberman at 
 jbeberman@bloomberg.net  